{"lemma":"حَبابٌ","slug":"حَبابٌ","root":"ح.ب.ب","root_slug":"ح-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6854","n6855","n6856"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"end, what something is aimed at"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"amity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"earring of one berry (حَبَّة (ḥabba))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a copiosity (bubble or streak) of water or sand on a surface etc."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beloved, friend"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"snake","tags":["euphemistic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح ب ب (ḥ b b). See also عُبَاب (ʕubāb, “billows”) from the root ع ب ب (ʕ b b), and مَغَبَّة (maḡabba) from the root غ ب ب (ḡ b b) also means “end”."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6854","headword_ar":"حَبَابٌ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAbuka","text_ar":"حَبَابُكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thine utmost:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the utmost of thy power:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the utmost of thy love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thine endeavour"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahodika","text_ar":"جَهْدِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juhaAdaAka","text_ar":"جُهَادَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaAdaAka","text_ar":"حُمَادَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quSaAraAka","text_ar":"قُصَارَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunaAmaAka","text_ar":"غُنَامَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuEaAmaAka","text_ar":"نُعَامَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]). (K. [In the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juhodika","text_ar":"جُهْدِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAbuka ka*aA","text_ar":"حَبَابُكَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAbk A^ano tafoEala *`lika","text_ar":"حبابك اَنْ تَفْعَلَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAbk A^ano yakuwna *`lika","text_ar":"حبابك اَنْ يَكُونَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thine utmost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the utmost of thy power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thy love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thine endeavour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will be such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy doing that,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that event's taking place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HababN","text_ar":"حَبَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water, (S, K,) and of sand, (K,) and of [the beverage called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but it is said that the third word applies particularly to water: (TA:) or the first signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"water, (As, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling variegated work:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waves"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that follow one another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bubbles"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) of water, (S, K,) or of wine, (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that float upon the surface;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also the second (AHn, A) and the third: (AHn, TA:) [it is a coll. gen. n., in this sense, of which the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to IDrd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbbu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"حببُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAbu","text_ar":"حبابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='i","text_ar":"المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takas~aruhu","text_ar":"تَكَسَّرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken surface, of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as is seen when it is slightly fretted by wind, and when it flows over uneven ground]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tirota biEubaAbihaA wafuzota","text_ar":"طِرْتَ بِعُبَابِهَا وَفُزْتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHabaAbihaA","text_ar":"بِحَبَابِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad. of 'Alee, relating to Aboo-Bekr, is explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast outrun others, and attained to the place where the flood of El-Islám collects, and reached the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"springs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof, and drunk the purest of it, and become possessor of its excellencies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[this is the only explanation of it that I have found:] but it is also otherwise explained. (Hr and others, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eb","text_ar":"عب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAbN","text_ar":"حَبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dew-drops;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dew"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is on trees &c. in the evening."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) It is said in a trad., of the inhabitants of Paradise, that their food shall turn into a sweat like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAb Almsok","text_ar":"حباب المسْك"},{"kind":"text","text":", by which is meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Musky dew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"musky bubbles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","TA","As","A","AHn","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n6855","headword_ar":"حُبَابٌ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a serpent not of a malignant species:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) accord. to some; (S;) but said to be so only because a serpent is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoTaAn","text_ar":"شَيْطَان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A 'Obeyd, S, TA.) ―         -b2-  And a pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] of which the sing. [or n. un.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAbapN","text_ar":"حُبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAbapu","text_ar":"حُبَابَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain black aquatic insect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small animal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u HubaAbK","text_ar":"اُمُّ حُبَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The present world;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) metonymically used in this sense. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","IAth","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n6856","headword_ar":"حِبَابٌ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AD%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8/","headword_ar":"حباب الله","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=113804#bf82a5","body_html":"حباب الله<br>كثير الحب لله سبحانه."}]}}